      <section id="footer">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-8 col-12-medium">
              <section>
                <header>
                  <h2>Why mosaigo?</h2>
                </header>
                <div class="row">
                  <div class="col-6">
                    <ul class="default">
                      <li><strong>Composition over configuration.</strong> Pipelines are assembled from independent steps, not configured from a mega-YAML.</li>
                      <li><strong>The compiler is your first reviewer.</strong> Go generics catch payload mismatches at build time.</li>
                      <li><strong>Metadata is not optional.</strong> Every step describes itself completely. That powers validation, catalogs, Studio, and the API.</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-6">
                    <ul class="default">
                      <li><strong>Steps don't know where they live.</strong> A step works with domain types, not infrastructure. Ports define contracts.</li>
                      <li><strong>Fail comprehensively, not fast.</strong> The validator collects every issue into a serializable list. You see all problems at once.</li>
                      <li><strong>Stdlib unless proven otherwise.</strong> slog, not logrus. net/http, not fiber. Every dependency earns its place.</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </section>
            </div>
